    "narrative": "The standout play for the Austin Waves today is undeniably **Gunnar Henderson**, who anchors our lineup with a dominant 81.88 efficiency score. Facing Kelly, he benefits from a 16% park factor boost and, crucially, a slow delivery profile from the mound that creates an 87% probability of a successful stolen base, aligning perfectly with our mandate to hunt scarcity. While **Josh Jung** (62.36) and **Jacob Wilson** (61.64) also project as strong starts, **Gunnar Henderson** holds the highest ceiling due to the confluence of his leadoff position and a favorable platoon matchup. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** provides a robust 70.49 efficiency, fueled by a significant 14% boost from his platoon advantage against Keller, who remains a targetable arm in today's slate.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the bench, where **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.06) narrowly missed the final cut. Despite his strong underlying xwOBA, his efficiency was capped by a difficult matchup against Misiorowski and a lower ceiling for category contribution compared to the high-upside profiles of **Brady House** or **Jackson Merrill**. We are also monitoring a 39% rain risk for **Miguel Vargas**, whose 57.38 score is contingent on him securing those leadoff plate appearances; should the weather shift, we have sufficient depth to pivot. Caution is advised with **Luis Robert Jr.** (44.07); despite favorable wind conditions, his efficiency is suppressed by an elite opposing pitcher in Yamamoto and a high risk of being held on the basepaths, making him a marginal start that we are only deploying due to his unique physical tools.",
